Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%grams}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{1%and a half} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat.

> If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} before baking.

Once hot, add the sliced mushrooms and onion. Stir-fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and half the garlic. Cook until evaporated, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @risotto rice{175%grams}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the @boiled water{600%ml} for the stock and @vegetable stock paste{20%grams} into the pan.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Rocket Pesto ==

Meanwhile, chop a quarter of the @wild rocket{40%grams} as finely as you can.

Pop it into a small #bowl{} with a quarter of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Mix in the olive oil, then set your rocket pesto aside.

== Portobello Mushrooms ==

Thinly slice the @portobello mushrooms{2}.

When the risotto has 10 mins left, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the portobello mushrooms and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds} more, then remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven. Stir through the @butter{20%grams} and remaining grated hard Italian style cheese.

> Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the risotto between your #bowls{}, then top with the sliced portobello mushrooms and your rocket pesto.

Serve the remaining rocket alongside drizzled with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Enjoy!